add maven builder to eclipse project
don't depend on dependency injection for scope since the injector may not have been set up yet
add inject to shared preferences provider constructor
switch to using context scoping switch to keeping the injector in Application instead of module
don't try to make injector until onCreate
move most of framework configuration to GuiceApplication add sample usage
change way i do modules to make testcases (which don't run inside a GuiceApplication) work
don't crash when running inside android test runner
took injection out of GuiceApplication, and moved it to a new class called GuiceInjectableApplication. GuiceInjectableApplication is identical to the old GuiceApplicaiton.
Updated Astroboy to get it work with the current robo-guice code.

Patch for issue 6 : http://code.google.com/p/robo-guice/issues/detail?id=6 Added createInjector method, and overridable addApplicationModules method. Added documentation for GuiceApplication, so that users know how to use it. Also fixed Astroboy so that it works with this patch.
Updated Astroboy to show how to inject a collaborator. The collabotor also get injected an AstroboyApplication (this is to show how to get an application injected)
updating version number to reflect changed apis
some name changes to avoid confusion with android services

get rid of hardcoded sdk location
getInjector and createInjector need to be synchronized to prevent the accidental creation of multiple injectors
configuration to try to publish artifacts to java.net--HG--nbranch : mvn2.java.netn
use a default shared prefs name unless otherwise specified
update pom.xml to publish to java.net
added ability to requestStaticInjection for @InjectResource if you're using AbstractAndroidModule
update astroboy sample to use AbstractAndroidModule
Patch for issue 25 (http://code.google.com/p/robo-guice/issues/detail?id=25) Astroboy aims at Android 1.6 when it could aim at Android 1.5
Patch for issue 26 : http://code.google.com/p/robo-guice/issues/detail?id=26 getInjector needs to be synchronized only when guice is null.
Updated documentation to take into account the recent evolving of AndroidAbstractModule
Patch for issue 31 : http://code.google.com/p/robo-guice/issues/detail?id=31 Remove synchronized keyword from createInjector. Added some javadoc to getInjector
Patch for issue 27 : http://code.google.com/p/robo-guice/issues/detail?id=27 Do not use Arrays.asList when the parameter is not an array.
Updated javadoc of GuiceApplication : added style and new lines. Added javadoc for configure method.
Added javadoc to GuiceActivity and it's related sisters.
updated Javadoc to tell users to subclass AbstractModule instead of directly implement Module
Added Javadoc on DefaultXXX annotations. Updated InjectExtra javadoc

Patch for issue 32 : http://code.google.com/p/robo-guice/issues/detail?id=32 Getting rid of @DefaultXXX annotation Added an optional parameter to InjectExtra annotation. Update ExtrasListener : removing any @DefaultXXX reference, and taking into account the optional parameter. A reformat occured while I was patching, so one might see more changes what I really changed. Sorry about that, we really need to share eclipse formatting settingsUpdated Astroboy to add an optional=true parameter to the InjectExtra annotation.n
Updated Astroboy to add android:debuggable=true to the Manifest (to enable debugging the app on a real device)
Removed DefaultXXX annotations (they are useless now)
Updated samples to show the different possibilities when using @InjectExtra
Wooops, forgot to add Tobio activity (a new activity that immediately starts DoctorTenma, adding extras to the intent ;-) .
Patch for issue 28 : http://code.google.com/p/robo-guice/issues/detail?id=28 Not instanciating guice related stuff before any GuiceActivity is used.
Example to show how to convert extras to instances, using a provider
Added copyright+license headers to all source java files
Patch for issue 3 : http://code.google.com/p/robo-guice/issues/detail?id=3 Pluggable convert mechanism for extras injection
behavior changes coming, so update version to 0.5-SNAPSHOT
get rid of weird head--HG--nrename : pom.xml => robo-guice/pom.xmln
first attempt at getting two stage injection working--HG--nbranch : two-stage-injectionn
fix exception when trying to inject a resource into a field of primitive type
Added Javadoc on ContextScoped and ExtraConverter
Bind Application injections to the unique Application instance Patch for issue 39 : http://code.google.com/p/robo-guice/issues/detail?id=39
ResourcesProvider should be a singleton Patch for issue 4 : http://code.google.com/p/robo-guice/issues/detail?id=40

GuiceApplicationProvider depends on an activity => what about singleton scopes ? Patch for issue 42 : http://code.google.com/p/robo-guice/issues/detail?id=42 Application is now available from the singleton scope, and the provider does not depend anymore on an activity.
Get rid of ViewResourceProvider and StringResourceProvider + Provide XXXResourceFactory Patch for issue 41 : http://code.google.com/p/robo-guice/issues/detail?id=41 Plus a usage example in Astroboy.

Yes! Bind Application AND SUBCLASSES to the unique Application instance Patch for issue 39 : http://code.google.com/p/robo-guice/issues/detail?id=39 I also updated AstroboyModule (only one binding allowed for a class)
Setting wider scopes for some providers, + lazy init (synchronized) of providers Patch for issue 40 : http://code.google.com/p/robo-guice/issues/detail?id=40
merge from pierre's branch.Left out changes to SystemServiceProvider and SharedPreferencesProvider for nown

split InjectResource and InjectView into two separate conceptsNOTE: THIS COMMIT BREAKS BACKWARD COMPATIBILITYnnAny activities that previously used @InjectResource to inject a viewnwill need to be updated to use @InjectView insteadnn--HG--nbranch : two-stage-injectionn
move injection to onCreate, with the exception of View injection, which is deferred until setContentView--HG--nbranch : two-stage-injectionn
merge from two-stage-injector branchNOTE: DEFINITELY BREAKS BACKWARD COMPATIBILITYn
